main event: On July 1, 1953, personnel from West Coast Airlines and a Navy pilot observed an unidentified flying object over La Grande, Oregon.
interesting points: The object exhibited fast maneuvers and then disappeared,No physical evidence was found to support the sighting,Weather conditions were clear with 25-mile visibility,The object was described as silent with no trails or exhaust,The sighting lasted approximately 15 minutes.
witness description: West Coast Airlines personnel and a Navy pilot
